Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:00:57.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,我还会问自己\N{\rEng}I still ask myself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.77,0:01:01.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,当初到底该不该离开他的海上浮城\N{\rEng}if I did the right thing when I abandoned his floating city.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.40,0:01:04.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,而且并不仅仅是为了那份工作\N{\rEng}And I don't mean only for the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.61,0:01:09.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,而是那样的一个朋友\N{\rEng}The fact is, a friend like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.11,0:01:11.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,真正的好友\N{\rEng}a real friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.35,0:01:14.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,这辈子不会有第二个了\N{\rEng}you won't meet one again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.62,0:01:18.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你决定就此离开大海\N{\rEng}If you just decide to hang up your sea legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.38,0:01:23.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想让双脚踏在坚实的大地上\N{\rEng}if you just want to feel something more solid beneath your feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.10,0:01:30.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,可这样一来  你再也听不到神一般的琴声了\N{\rEng}and if then you no loner hear the music of the gods around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.06,0:01:34.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是  就像他常说的那样\N{\rEng}But, like he used to say:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.54,0:01:40.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,只要你还有一个好故事  还可以找个人讲讲\N{\rEng}"You're never really done for as long as you got a good story...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.56,0:01:42.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,就还不算完\N{\rEng}and someone to tell it to."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.24,0:01:46.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,问题是\N{\rEng}Trouble is ...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.96,0:01:51.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,没人相信我的故事\N{\rEng}nobody'd believe a single word of my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.97,0:02:07.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(194,180)\fn方正小标宋_GBK\c&HFFFFFF&\fad(505,508)\fs25\bord0\shad0\b0}蒂姆·罗斯
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.07,0:02:19.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,180)\fn方正小标宋_GBK\c&HFFFFFF&\fad(504,499)\fs25\bord0\shad0\b0}普路特·泰勒·文斯
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.10,0:02:21.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,每次都是如此\N{\rEng}It happened everytime...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.95,0:02:24.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,总有个人会抬起头  看到她\N{\rEng}someone would look up and see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.56,0:02:27.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,真是无法理解\N{\rEng}It's difficult to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.14,0:02:32.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,船上有一千多个人呢\N{\rEng}there were more than a thousand of us on that ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.27,0:02:35.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,旅行的有钱人  移民\N{\rEng}travelling richfolk, immigrants,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.41,0:02:37.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,怪人  还有我们\N{\rEng}and strange people, and us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.12,0:02:40.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,但每次总有那么一个\N{\rEng}Yet, there was always one!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.70,0:02:44.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,就有那么一个人  会先看到她\N{\rEng}One guy alone who would see her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:48.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,或许他当时正坐在那儿吃东西\N{\rEng}Maybe he was just sitting there eating,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.82,0:02:50.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,或是在甲板上散步\N{\rEng}or walking on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.94,0:02:53.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,或许他正在提裤子\N{\rEng}Maybe he was just fixing his pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.56,0:02:57.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,他抬了一下头  冲大海扫了一眼\N{\rEng}He'd look up for a second, a quick glance out to sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:02:59.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后就看见了她\N{\rEng}and he'd see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.36,0:03:05.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,于是他定在了原地  心跳开始加速\N{\rEng}Then he'd just stand there, rooted to the spot, his heart racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.83,0:03:10.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,每一次  我发誓  真他妈是每一次啊\N{\rEng}And every time, every damn time, I swear,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.70,0:03:15.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,他会转过身  对船上的所有人\N{\rEng}he'd turn to us, towards the ship towards everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.72,0:03:17.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,大喊\N{\rEng}and scream...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.96,0:03:20.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,美国\N{\rEng}America!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.67,0:03:37.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,190)\fn方正小标宋_GBK\c&HFFFFFF&\fad(506,508)\fs30\bord0\shad0\b0}海  上  钢  琴  师
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.35,0:04:18.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(194,190)\fn方正小标宋_GBK\c&HFFFFFF&\fad(404,309)\fs14\bord0\shad0\b0}原创音乐   作曲  编曲  指挥\N{\fs25}埃尼奥·莫里康内
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.33,0:04:53.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,纽约\N{\rEng}New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.00,0:04:57.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(190,230)\fn方正小标宋_GBK\c&HFFFFFF&\fad(404,308)\fs15\bord0\shad0\b0}导演\N\N\N\N\N\N{\fs25}朱塞佩·托纳多雷
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.20,0:05:03.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,第一个看见美国的人\N{\rEng}The one who sees America first.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.74,0:05:06.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,每艘船上都有一个\N{\rEng}There's one on every ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.10,0:05:11.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,别以为这只是意外  或是视错觉\N{\rEng}And don't be thinking it's an accident or some optical illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.82,0:05:13.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是命运\N{\rEng}It's destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.03,0:05:15.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,这特殊的一刻\N{\rEng}Those are people
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:20.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,一直就刻在他们的生命中\N{\rEng}who always have that precise instant stamped on their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.12,0:05:24.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们还小的时候  如果你看他们的眼睛\N{\rEng}And when they were kids, you could look into their eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.29,0:05:30.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,仔细地看  就已经能看到她的倩影\N{\rEng}and if you looked carefully enough you'd already see her,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.81,0:05:33.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,美国\N{\rEng}America.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.62,0:05:44.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,我也见过好几次美国了\N{\rEng}And I've seen a few Americas!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:47.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,在船上六年  每年跨洋五次\N{\rEng}Six years on that ship, five crossings a year:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.24,0:05:50.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,欧洲  美国往返\N{\rEng}Europe, America and back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.91,0:05:53.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,总是泡在海上\N{\rEng}Always soaking in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.29,0:05:55.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,等你上了陆地\N{\rEng}When you stepped on land
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.71,0:05:57.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,撒尿都要撒到外面\N{\rEng}you couldn't even piss straight in the john.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.21,0:06:01.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,厕所倒是稳稳地固定在地上\N{\rEng}It was steady. The john, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.43,0:06:04.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,你却像个傻子似的摇摇摆摆\N{\rEng}but you'd keep bobbing like an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:10.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,下船不是难事  但把海洋抛在脑后...\N{\rEng}You can get off a ship all right, but off the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.61,0:06:11.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,我正要关门\N{\rEng}I was just closing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:14.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,有什么事吗\N{\rEng}What can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.29,0:06:19.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,我登船时才24岁\N{\rEng}When I boarded I was twenty-four years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.18,0:06:23.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,当时我只在乎一件事\N{\rEng}and I only cared about one thing in life
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:27.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,吹小号\N{\rEng}playing the trumpet
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.54,0:06:33.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,我要卖掉这个\N{\rEng}I'm selling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.89,0:06:39.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,康恩小号\N{\rEng}A Conn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.87,0:06:41.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,不赖啊\N{\rEng}Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.26,0:06:50.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,这可是上好的铜管乐器\N{\rEng}Best brass money can buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.94,0:06:57.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,6镑10先令  不能再多了\N{\rEng}Six pounds, ten shillings. Best I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:59.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,这小号是我的一生啊  先生\N{\rEng}That horn's my whole life, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:01.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,但即使我不是个人物\N{\rEng}But even just being a nobody
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.56,0:07:04.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,这小号也不止这个价钱啊\N{\rEng}it's got to be worth more than twenty lousy bucks!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.26,0:07:06.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果这么说\N{\rEng}If that's how things are,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:09.18,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}1克朗=5先令
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:09.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,那它连半个{\u1}克朗{\u0}都不值了\N{\rEng}I suppose it's barely worth half a crown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.57,0:07:12.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,出去时麻烦顺手关门\N{\rEng}Shut the door when you leave, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.30,0:07:21.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  老爹  你赢了\N{\rEng}Okay, Pops, you win!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.33,0:07:27.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,你刚刚买下了一件音乐历史\N{\rEng}You just bought yourself a piece of musical history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.68,0:07:32.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,听我一句劝\N{\rEng}Now, if you want my advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.92,0:07:38.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,去吃顿好的吧\N{\rEng}go out, treat yourself to a decent meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.72,0:08:00.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,让我再吹一次吧\N{\rEng}At least let me play it one last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.13,0:08:02.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,年轻人  我没那个闲工夫\N{\rEng}Young man I don't have time to waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.71,0:08:06.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.77,0:08:11.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,快点  我要关门了\N{\rEng}Hurry up, then, I'm closing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.60,0:08:13.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.05,0:09:39.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,如出一辙  是不是\N{\rEng}Two peas in a pod, wouldn't you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.82,0:09:43.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是你刚刚吹奏的曲子啊\N{\rEng}It's the music you were just playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.58,0:09:44.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,它叫什么\N{\rEng}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:49.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,这曲子没有名字\N{\rEng}It doesn't have a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.30,0:09:56.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,只有几个人有幸听过\N{\rEng}Just a handful of people have had the privilege of hearing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:03.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,这曲风\N{\rEng}That style.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.57,0:10:06.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,我今早上一直在想\N{\rEng}I was wondering since this morning, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.55,0:10:11.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,就是猜不出这个厉害的钢琴师是谁\N{\rEng}I can't work out who this amazing piano player is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.28,0:10:14.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,你应该没听说过他\N{\rEng}I don't think you've ever heard of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:15.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,他是谁\N{\rEng}Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.54,0:10:16.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果我告诉你\N{\rEng}If I told you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.33,0:10:19.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个钢琴师根本没存在过\N{\rEng}that this pianist never existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.54,0:10:21.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,那也绝不为过\N{\rEng}I wouldn't be lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.20,0:10:23.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,我讨厌秘密\N{\rEng}I don't like secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:27.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,说吧  美国佬  这究竟是谁\N{\rEng}Come on now, Yank, who the devil is playing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:31.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的秘密\N{\rEng}It's my secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.68,0:10:48.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,那是这该死的世纪的第一年\N{\rEng}It was the first year of this frigging century,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.17,0:10:52.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,此话出自弗吉尼亚号上一个不知名的黑人司炉\N{\rEng}as defined by an unknown colored coal stoker on the Virginian.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.90,0:10:54.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,妈逼有钱的混蛋\N{\rEng}Fucking rich-ass bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.86,0:10:58.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,就扔下些烟头和脏手绢\N{\rEng}Can't lose nothing but cigarette butts and dirty-ass handkerchiefs!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.11,0:11:03.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,都不丢块手表\N{\rEng}Can't lose no watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.12,0:11:07.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,哪怕一块破爱尔近表  或是袖扣都没有\N{\rEng}not even a beat-up Elgin or a sorry-ass cufflink.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.79,0:11:11.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想什么呢  连枚妈逼的假戒指都没有\N{\rEng}What am I talking about? Not even a fake fucking ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.17,0:11:15.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,瞧瞧啊  一整支雪茄\N{\rEng}Hey, look here, a whole cigar!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.70,0:11:18.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,肯定有人在晚会上玩傻了\N{\rEng}Must've been somebody poor at the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.44,0:11:24.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,瞧这些破烂  真混蛋\N{\rEng}Look at this shit! Nasty fucker!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.66,0:11:27.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,有钱的混蛋\N{\rEng}Damn rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.91,0:11:30.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,什么都不落下  欠了你的钱就失忆了\N{\rEng}Don't forget nothing unless they owe you some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.66,0:11:38.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么在这儿\N{\rEng}What in the scuts you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.81,0:11:44.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,T·D·莱蒙斯{\fs14}[TD柠檬]\N{\rEng}T.D. Lemons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.00,0:11:56.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好啊  小莱蒙\N{\rEng}Howdy do there, Lemon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.47,0:11:58.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,移民的野种\N{\rEng}Immigrant bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.97,0:12:02.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,说得没错  移民就这德行\N{\rEng}You said it. That's the way the immigrants do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.22,0:12:03.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,在船上生下孩子\N{\rEng}Have a baby on the ship
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.51,0:12:06.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后扔下他  留给别人喂养\N{\rEng}and then leave on board another mouth to feed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.76,0:12:10.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,就这样躲过移民局的检查\N{\rEng}And, like that, avoid trouble with the immigration office!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.70,0:12:13.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,这样的孩子长大能干什么啊\N{\rEng}What's a boy like him going to be when he grows up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.37,0:12:14.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,又是个移民\N{\rEng}Another immigrant!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.22,0:12:18.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,别理那些混蛋  小莱蒙\N{\rEng}Don't pay those bastards, no mind Lemon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.95,0:12:20.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,吃吧  好孩子\N{\rEng}Go on, lap it up boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:25.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,这小子被人放在一等舱的钢琴上\N{\rEng}This one they left in first class on top the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:27.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,肯定是希望有个有钱人能来把他抱走\N{\rEng}They are hoping some rich guy will come and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.81,0:12:30.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,让他过好日子\N{\rEng}stick a silver spoon in his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.03,0:12:32.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,结果谁捡到这小猴子了呢\N{\rEng}And who does the little ape get instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.26,0:12:34.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个穷司炉\N{\rEng}A poor worthless stoker!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.58,0:12:37.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,有人拿你当冤大头呢  丹尼\N{\rEng}Someon is taking you for a sucker, Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.37,0:12:42.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们逍遥快活  留下烂摊子让你收拾\N{\rEng}They have the fun, you have the misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.26,0:12:46.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,去你们这些穷鬼  臭虫\N{\rEng}Fuck poverty, you stinking sewer rats!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.25,0:12:48.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,那盒子上写着TD\N{\rEng}T.D. was written on the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.82,0:12:50.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,你们这些蠢货知道那是什么意思吗\N{\rEng}Any of you shitheads know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.88,0:12:53.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,我忘了  你们都不识字\N{\rEng}I forgot, you all can't read!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.34,0:12:55.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,意思就是"谢谢  丹尼"\N{\rEng}It means, "Thanks, Danny." "Thanks, Danny"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.64,0:12:57.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们是把那孩子留给了我  我要养大他\N{\rEng}They left that boy for me and l'm keeping him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.66,0:12:59.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,你们都给我滚一边去\N{\rEng}Rest of you all can go fuck yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.67,0:13:03.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼  你打算管那小子叫什么\N{\rEng}Danny, what are you going to call the nino?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.85,0:13:06.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,这我还真没想过\N{\rEng}Hell, I didn't think about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.11,0:13:12.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,我要让他随我的名字  丹尼·布德曼\N{\rEng}To start off, I name him after me, Danny Boodman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.60,0:13:15.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后中间再加上TD\N{\rEng}Then l'll put T.D. in the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.27,0:13:18.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,有钱人的袖扣和衬衫上都写着中间名\N{\rEng}like the rich folks puts on their cufflinks in shirts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.23,0:13:21.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,加个中间名  立刻就上档次了  是不是\N{\rEng}That give it class, to put that in the middle, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.77,0:13:25.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,那些妈逼的律师名字中间也有首写字母\N{\rEng}All fucking lawyers gots initials in the middle of their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:28.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,我的律师就叫乔纳森·P·T·K·旺达\N{\rEng}Well, my lawyer was Jonathan P.T.K. Wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.82,0:13:32.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果我儿子长大当了律师  我就亲手杀了他\N{\rEng}My son grow up to be a lawyer, I swear I'll kill him myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.37,0:13:36.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过我还是要叫他丹尼·布德曼·T·D·莱蒙\N{\rEng}But the boy's name is still going to be Danny Boodman T.D. Lemon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:39.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,他又不是妈逼公爵的儿子  丹尼\N{\rEng}He ain't the son of no fucking duke, Danny!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.41,0:13:42.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是周二找到他的  就喊他周二吧\N{\rEng}You found him on a Tuesday, call him Tuesday!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.98,0:13:47.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,你个黑鬼  也没看上去那么蠢嘛\N{\rEng}You ain't as dumb as you look, colored boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.76,0:13:49.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,我是在这该死的新世纪的\N{\rEng}I found him the first month
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.66,0:13:53.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,第一年的第一个月找到了他\N{\rEng}of the first year of this frigging new century,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.09,0:13:57.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以我要叫他  1900\N{\rEng}so I'm calling him Nineteen Hundred!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.17,0:14:00.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,1900  那是个数字啊\N{\rEng}Nineteen Hundred? But that's a number!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:02.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,的确是个数字  现在也是名字了\N{\rEng}It was a number, now it's a name!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.89,0:14:08.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼·布德曼·T·D·莱蒙·1900\N{\rEng}Danny Boodman T.D. Lemon Nineteen Hundred!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.75,0:14:12.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼  你的小宝宝不太开心呢\N{\rEng}Danny, your little bambino is not so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.06,0:14:14.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,快点  快走\N{\rEng}Come on, hurry, Hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.81,0:14:24.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,天呐  这么个小家伙居然拉出这么多屎来\N{\rEng}Damn. How can something that small shit so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.53,0:14:32.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,小1900就是这样慢慢长大\N{\rEng}And that's how little Nineteen Hundred grew up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:35.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,就在这一整条船大的摇篮里\N{\rEng}inside that cradle as big as a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.75,0:14:38.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是丹尼担心会有人因为\N{\rEng}But, since Danny was afraid they'd take him away
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.95,0:14:42.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,法律文书和签证的关系而把他带走\N{\rEng}on account of some business concerning documents and visas,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.28,0:14:45.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,这孩子小时候一直躲在\N{\rEng}the boy lived his early years always hiding
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:47.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗吉尼亚号的船舱里\N{\rEng}in the belly of the Virginian.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.00,0:15:10.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,好了  你自己来试试\N{\rEng}Okay, now try one for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.05,0:15:14.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,来  拿手指着这些单词\N{\rEng}Now, look here. Put your finger up here against these words,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:16.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,这样字就不会乱跑了\N{\rEng}so the letters can't run off on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.64,0:15:17.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,芒...\N{\rEng}"Man"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.02,0:15:19.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,不错  继续读\N{\rEng}All right, keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.51,0:15:21.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,果\N{\rEng}"Go"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.73,0:15:23.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,继续\N{\rEng}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.59,0:15:24.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,妈\N{\rEng}"Ma"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.70,0:15:26.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,差一点了\N{\rEng}Just a little bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.19,0:15:27.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,妈\N{\rEng}"Ma".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.02,0:15:31.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,你读得可真好啊  莱蒙\N{\rEng}Boy, you read like a God, Lemon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.52,0:15:33.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,来  把他们连着读\N{\rEng}Now, go on, put them all together,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.04,0:15:34.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,就像锅炉气门那样\N{\rEng}kind of like them boiler valves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.91,0:15:37.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,读吧\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.40,0:15:45.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,芒...果...妈妈\N{\rEng}"Man... go...Mama"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.60,0:15:50.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,芒果妈妈  好的  继续\N{\rEng}Mango Mama. All right. Keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.39,0:15:55.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,拽...缰...绳\N{\rEng}"Ya-nk my ch-ain"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.04,0:16:00.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼  你怎么笑得这么开心\N{\rEng}Danny, why are you laughing so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.79,0:16:03.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,这都是马的名字啊  你说这多好玩\N{\rEng}Because these are names of horses. Don't that make you laugh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.73,0:16:06.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些马的名字真逗死我了  你看这儿\N{\rEng}I'm just crazy about these horses' names. Look at this one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.38,0:16:08.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,昨天在克利夫兰赛跑\N{\rEng}Ran yesterday at Cleveland.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.32,0:16:11.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,快乐舞蹈家\N{\rEng}"Ha-ppy Hoo-fers".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.39,0:16:14.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,听啊\N{\rEng}Listen to this
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:17.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,俏皮小妞\N{\rEng}"Sa-ssy La-ssy".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.09,0:16:18.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,俏皮小妞\N{\rEng}Sassy Lassy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.25,0:16:22.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,还有这个  "火辣妈妈"\N{\rEng}And this one, "Red Hot Mama"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:27.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈是什么  丹尼\N{\rEng}What's a mama, Danny?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.01,0:16:30.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\rEng}A mama?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.06,0:16:34.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈就是马啊\N{\rEng}A mama's a horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.43,0:16:35.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,马吗\N{\rEng}A horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.68,0:16:36.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,赛马\N{\rEng}Racehorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.83,0:16:39.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,而且  要我说\N{\rEng}Matter of fact, you know what I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.09,0:16:40.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈是这世上最好的马\N{\rEng}Mama's the best horse in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.61,0:16:43.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,纯种马  你赌妈妈  准赢不输\N{\rEng}Thoroughbred, you bet on a mama, you always win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.00,0:16:53.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,谭诺·德马托  柠檬之王\N{\rEng}"Tano D'Amato The King of Lemons"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.97,0:16:56.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸  那手指着这儿读\N{\rEng}Dad, put your finger here and read.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.09,0:17:01.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,TD不是"谢谢  丹尼"的意思\N{\rEng}T.D. Doesn't mean "Thanks, Danny"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.17,0:17:04.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,这娘娘腔是谁\N{\rEng}Who's this pansy ass?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.90,0:17:06.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,你今晚读够了\N{\rEng}That's enough reading for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.26,0:17:09.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,读书太多对你没好处\N{\rEng}Too much reading's bad for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.51,0:17:12.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,还有什么不好  丹尼\N{\rEng}What else is bad, Danny?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.79,0:17:15.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗吉尼亚号之外的一切都不好\N{\rEng}Everything off the Virginian is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.80,0:17:18.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,一切一切\N{\rEng}Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.53,0:17:22.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,陆地上有鲨鱼  会把你生吞\N{\rEng}They got sharks on the land, they eat you alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.06,0:17:23.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,你要离得远远的  听着没\N{\rEng}You keep away from they, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.48,0:17:26.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼  孤儿院是什么\N{\rEng}Danny, what's an orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.20,0:17:31.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,孤儿院就像座大监狱\N{\rEng}Well, a orphanage is like a great big prison
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.49,0:17:33.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,专门关押没有孩子的人\N{\rEng}where they lock up folks that ain't got kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.52,0:17:38.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么如果你没有我  就会被关进孤儿院吗\N{\rEng}So if I wasn't with you they would put you in an orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.83,0:17:43.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,没错  小莱蒙  晚安了\N{\rEng}You got that right, little Lemon. Night-night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.59,0:18:20.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,当心  丹尼\N{\rEng}Watch out, Danny!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.55,0:18:26.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼\N{\rEng}Danny!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.10,0:18:34.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,把他翻过来\N{\rEng}Roll him over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.07,0:18:39.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,叫个医生来\N{\rEng}Call a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.43,0:18:41.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,-去把医生叫来  -医生\N{\rEng}- Get the doctor.  - Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.90,0:18:43.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼  该死的  说话啊\N{\rEng}Danny, you bloody cow. Talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.63,0:18:49.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,背后挨了一下而已  伙计们\N{\rEng}Ain't nothing but a pat on the back, boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.38,0:18:51.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,"老天爷"\N{\rEng}Holy Shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.02,0:18:58.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,和"好时光"\N{\rEng}and Times Were Good
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.43,0:19:03.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,被取消资格\N{\rEng}was disqualified.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.46,0:19:07.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,"俏母牛"\N{\rEng}Saucy Bossy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.95,0:19:11.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,老丹尼三天后才断了气\N{\rEng}It took him three days to go toes up, old Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.61,0:19:15.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,当时正值芝加哥的第六场比赛\N{\rEng}He let go on the sixth race in Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.47,0:19:20.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,"饮用水"领先"蔬菜汤"两段\N{\rEng}Drinkable Water by two lengths over Vegetable Soup,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.13,0:19:22.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,领先"蓝基金"五段\N{\rEng}and five over Blue Foudation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.40,0:19:26.62,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}圣经  旧约《诗篇》23:4
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.40,0:19:26.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,我虽然行过死亡的幽谷\N{\rEng}"Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.71,0:19:29.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,也不怕遭害  因为您与我同在\N{\rEng}"I will fear no evil, for thou art with me."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.60,0:19:32.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,您的杖  您的杆安抚着我\N{\rEng}Thy rod and thy staff they comfort me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.85,0:19:35.93,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}谢谢  丹尼
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.39,0:19:36.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,我将永远居于上帝的殿堂\N{\rEng}And I will dwell in the house of the lord forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.20,0:19:42.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,以圣父  圣子  圣灵之名\N{\rEng}In the name of the Father and of the Son, and of the Holy Ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.40,0:19:43.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,阿门\N{\rEng}Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.42,0:19:57.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,音乐{\fs14}[日语]\N{\rEng}おんがく.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.91,0:20:00.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,音乐\N{\rEng}Music.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.44,0:20:14.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,1900那时八岁\N{\rEng}Nineteen Hundred was eight years old then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.30,0:20:19.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,大概已经在欧洲和美国之间\N{\rEng}He'd made the trip between Europe and America
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.33,0:20:21.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,来回五十次了吧\N{\rEng}about fifty times, I imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.13,0:20:25.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,大海就是他的家\N{\rEng}The ocean was his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.66,0:20:28.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,他从未踏上过陆地  从来没有\N{\rEng}He never set foot on dry land. Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.85,0:20:31.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,他在港口无数次看见过陆地\N{\rEng}He'd seen it from the ports a hundred times,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.72,0:20:34.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,却从未下过船\N{\rEng}but he never got off the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.13,0:20:36.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,问题是\N{\rEng}Problem was
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.50,0:20:39.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,在世人眼里  他压根就不存在\N{\rEng}as far as the world was concerned he didn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.17,0:20:43.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有一个城市  教区  医院\N{\rEng}There wasn't a city, a parish, a hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.33,0:20:45.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,监狱  或是棒球队\N{\rEng}jail or baseball team
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.69,0:20:47.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,曾出现过他的名字\N{\rEng}that had his name any place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.28,0:20:49.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,他没有国籍\N{\rEng}He didn't have a country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.98,0:20:51.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,连出生日期都没有\N{\rEng}He didn't even have a birth date.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.90,0:20:53.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,也没有家人\N{\rEng}No family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:57.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,他八岁了  但严格来说\N{\rEng}He was eight years old, but officially,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.28,0:20:59.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,他根本就没出生\N{\rEng}he had never even been born.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.35,0:21:20.17,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}禁止入内
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.56,0:22:35.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,船长  船长  醒醒\N{\rEng}Captain! Captain, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.02,0:23:24.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,他叫什么\N{\rEng}What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.50,0:23:26.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,1900\N{\rEng}Nineteen Hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.22,0:23:29.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是曲子  那孩子\N{\rEng}Not the song, the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.46,0:23:30.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,1900\N{\rEng}Nineteen Hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.52,0:23:32.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,和那曲子一样\N{\rEng}Like the song!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.90,0:24:04.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,1900\N{\rEng}Nineteen Hundred,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.25,0:24:07.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是完全违反规定的\N{\rEng}all of this is entirely against the regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.42,0:24:11.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,去他妈的规定\N{\rEng}Fuck the regulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.96,0:24:18.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,但我还是不明白\N{\rEng}But I don't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.25,0:24:21.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,这一切和这唱片有什么关系\N{\rEng}what the record has to do with any of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.48,0:24:23.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,这张唱片不该存在\N{\rEng}This record shouldn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.70,0:24:28.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,唯一的母带  刚刻制完就被毁掉了\N{\rEng}The only existing matrix was destroyed right after it was cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.03,0:24:31.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,可这确实是母带\N{\rEng}Well, this is a matrix.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.73,0:24:37.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,用来进行现场录音挺方便的\N{\rEng}Quite handy for on-the-spot recordings that sort of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.18,0:24:42.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是怎么搞到这个的\N{\rEng}How did you get your hands on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.18,0:24:46.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,我今天花了好长时间\N{\rEng}I spend the better part of the day
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.89,0:24:48.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,把它的碎片拼起来\N{\rEng}putting the bits and pieces together.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.90,0:24:50.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,我是偶然发现的\N{\rEng}I found them by accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.13,0:24:54.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,藏在那两台钢琴中一台里面\N{\rEng}Hidden inside one of those two pianos.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.19,0:24:57.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我从一个二手商人手里买来的\N{\rEng}I bought them from a second-hand dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.66,0:25:01.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们清空了普利茅斯的一艘老医务船\N{\rEng}They've emptied out an old hospital ship down at Plymouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.18,0:25:14.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,-就在那儿  伙计  -谢谢\N{\rEng}- It's over there, mate. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.81,0:26:12.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,慢点  慢点  滑轮慢一点\N{\rEng}Slow down. Slow down. Not so fast with that pulley.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.43,0:26:14.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,上面的  慢一点\N{\rEng}Easy up there, easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.38,0:26:16.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,小心点啊  这里面可不是香蕉\N{\rEng}Watch that, John. These aren't bananas, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.18,0:26:20.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,上面的  慢一点\N{\rEng}Easy up there, easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.84,0:26:42.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是哪里人\N{\rEng}Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.01,0:26:43.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,利物浦\N{\rEng}Liverpool.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.71,0:26:45.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,-做什么的  -我是理发师\N{\rEng}- What do you do? - I'm a barber.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.48,0:26:47.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,-把他签上  -非常感谢\N{\rEng}- Sign him on. - Thanks very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.60,0:26:50.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,下一个  你是做什么的\N{\rEng}Next. What's your trade?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.56,0:26:52.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,我是木匠\N{\rEng}I'm a carpenter,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.05,0:26:54.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,-还是个好技工  -出去  下一个\N{\rEng}- a good mechanic. - Get out ! Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.46,0:26:56.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是干什么的\N{\rEng}What do you do ?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.22,0:26:59.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,我是吹小号的\N{\rEng}I play the trumpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.57,0:27:02.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们船上已经有乐师了  下一个\N{\rEng}We've already got musicians on board. Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.34,0:27:30.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,他要上哪去\N{\rEng}Where the hell's he going ?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.25,0:28:08.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,那是什么音乐\N{\rEng}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.96,0:28:09.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.63,0:28:11.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,你不知道\N{\rEng}When you don't know what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.10,0:28:13.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,那就是爵士乐\N{\rEng}it's jazz!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.44,0:28:18.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,那是我一生最快乐的一天\N{\rEng}It was the happiest day of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.10,0:28:21.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,所有人眼里充满希望\N{\rEng}All those people with hope in their eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.12,0:28:23.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,道别声  汽笛声  不绝于耳\N{\rEng}The goodbyes, the sirens,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.67,0:28:26.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,那巨大的水上王国就要启程\N{\rEng}and that big floating world starting to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.92,0:28:31.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,这巨大的盛会  像是为我准备的\N{\rEng}It felt like one big party, a huge bash just for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.06,0:28:37.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,但三天后  大海厌倦了欢乐气氛\N{\rEng}But just three days later the ocean got tired of the festivities.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.27,0:29:12.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,康恩号\N{\rEng}Hey, Conn?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.71,0:29:14.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么了\N{\rEng}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.29,0:29:16.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,晕船了吗\N{\rEng}Lose your sea legs?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.53,0:29:20.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是新来的小号手吧\N{\rEng}You're the new trumpet man, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.01,0:29:21.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,你吹康恩号\N{\rEng}And you blow a Conn?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.72,0:29:25.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,跟我来\N{\rEng}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.44,0:29:28.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,我能结束你的痛苦\N{\rEng}I have a cure for your misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.31,0:29:30.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,跟我走\N{\rEng}Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.32,0:30:08.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,-劳驾  松下闸  -什么\N{\rEng}- Take the brakes off, please. - What!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.07,0:30:10.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,你疯了吧\N{\rEng}That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.88,0:30:11.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,相信我\N{\rEng}Trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.07,0:30:14.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,松开闸\N{\rEng}Just take the brakes off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.08,0:30:30.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,跳上来  坐我旁边\N{\rEng}Hop on next to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.76,0:30:33.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,你脑子有病吧\N{\rEng}What are you, some kind of nut case.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.39,0:30:36.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,你最好快点  否则就上不来了\N{\rEng}You better get on now or you never will.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.71,0:31:10.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,跟我说说  你有孩子吗\N{\rEng}Tell me something, do you have children?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.72,0:31:15.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,该死  你有一天会被关进孤儿院的\N{\rEng}Shit, they'll lock you up in the orphanage one of these days!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.89,0:31:16.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,他疯了\N{\rEng}He's nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.14,0:31:24.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,天啊  妈妈\N{\rEng}Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.49,0:31:26.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,你挺了解马的嘛\N{\rEng}I see you know your horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.27,0:31:28.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,-懂一点  -好样的\N{\rEng}- Just a litte. - Good man!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.04,0:32:59.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好  船长\N{\rEng}Good evening, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.44,0:33:00.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,来兜一圈吗\N{\rEng}Care for a ride?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.51,0:33:08.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,再说说那该死的窗户有多大\N{\rEng}Tell me again how big the fucking window was?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.70,0:33:10.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,真他妈的大\N{\rEng}What a big fucking window!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.63,0:33:16.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们要永远在这船上铲煤了\N{\rEng}You know, we're going to be shoveling coal on this ship till eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.92,0:33:18.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,可不是\N{\rEng}No shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.03,0:33:28.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,至少你知道长大以后会干什么\N{\rEng}Least you know what you'll be doing when you grow up!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.20,0:33:33.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,-康恩号  -怎么了\N{\rEng}- Hey, Conn. - What ?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.68,0:33:36.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,你从新奥尔良来的吧\N{\rEng}You're from New Orleans, right ?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.30,0:33:37.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道\N{\rEng}How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.48,0:33:40.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢那地方\N{\rEng}I love that town.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.17,0:33:43.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,真的吗  我好久没去了\N{\rEng}Really? I haven't been there in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.65,0:33:47.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,那儿的冬天很美\N{\rEng}In winter, it's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.65,0:33:51.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,三月时\N{\rEng}And in March,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.74,0:33:59.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,总会有那么一个下午  不期而至\N{\rEng}you can always count on one afternoon when you least expect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.89,0:34:02.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,大雾弥漫\N{\rEng}The fog slides in.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.56,0:34:08.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,乳白色的屏障就垂在街灯之下\N{\rEng}A milky barrier hangs just below the street lamps.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.29,0:34:11.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,把一切斩断\N{\rEng}It cuts everything off!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.74,0:34:14.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,就像雪白的刀刃\N{\rEng}Like a white blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.63,0:34:16.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,可神奇了\N{\rEng}And it's magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.87,0:34:21.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,房子的顶层不见了\N{\rEng}Houses lose their top floors,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.22,0:34:23.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,树枝也藏了起来\N{\rEng}trees lose their branches,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.98,0:34:27.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,圣路易斯大教堂的尖顶没了\N{\rEng}St. Louis Cathedral loses its spires,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.18,0:34:29.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,路人的脑袋不见了\N{\rEng}people passing by there lose their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.06,0:34:32.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,颈部以上的部分都不见了\N{\rEng}So from the neck up, everything disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.33,0:34:35.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,杰克逊广场上\N{\rEng}All you can see in Jackson Square
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.62,0:34:37.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,都是一堆没头的身体\N{\rEng}is a bunch of decapitated bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.59,0:34:40.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,磕磕绊绊  乱走乱撞  互相说\N{\rEng}stumbling around and bumping into each other saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.46,0:34:42.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,"你妈妈好吗  伙计"\N{\rEng}"How's your mama, man?"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.03,0:34:46.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,就是这样  很遗憾  不能持续很久\N{\rEng}That's it! Too bad it doesn't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.01,0:34:48.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,可你是怎么知道这些的\N{\rEng}But how do you know all these things?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.63,0:34:56.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,我登船之后\N{\rEng}You know, ever since I came on board,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.65,0:34:59.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,听到很多关于一个人的传言\N{\rEng}I've been hearing a lot of talk about a guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.48,0:35:03.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,据说他就生在这艘船上\N{\rEng}He's supposed to have been born on this ship
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.23,0:35:06.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,而且从未下过船\N{\rEng}and never been off it since.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.75,0:35:08.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,太疯狂了\N{\rEng}Crazy story.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.44,0:35:11.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,20年没踏上过陆地\N{\rEng}Twenty years without ever setting foot on land?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.92,0:35:12.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,27年\N{\rEng}Twenty-seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.94,0:35:17.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,据说这个人创作的音乐前所未闻\N{\rEng}They say this guy makes music that's never been heard before.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.55,0:35:18.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,我也听说过他\N{\rEng}I've heard of him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.51,0:35:23.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,我本来以为你就是那个人\N{\rEng}First off, I thought you were the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.77,0:35:26.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,-但有些地方不太对  -当然\N{\rEng}- But then something didn't add up. - Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.45,0:35:30.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我就想  他要是1900\N{\rEng}I figured, if he's Nineteen Hundred,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.12,0:35:33.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,怎么可能这么了解新奥尔良呢\N{\rEng}how could he know New Orleans so well?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.13,0:35:36.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为你肯定去过新奥尔良\N{\rEng}Because you've been to New Orleans.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.43,0:35:39.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果我说我从未去过那里\N{\rEng}Well, if I told you I'd never set foot in that town,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.73,0:35:40.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,你会相信吗\N{\rEng}would you believe me?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.72,0:35:48.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,不管你是谁  我是麦克斯·图尼\N{\rEng}Whoever you are, Max Tooney.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.69,0:35:50.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴认识你\N{\rEng}Glad to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.01,0:36:05.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,怎么样了\N{\rEng}How we doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.90,0:36:08.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们是要把它炸掉\N{\rEng}We're supposed to blow it up
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.48,0:36:11.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是等着鱼来把它啃光\N{\rEng}not wait for it to be eaten by the fishes!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.99,0:36:14.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,你们什么也不能炸\N{\rEng}You're not going to blow up a goddamn thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.09,0:36:16.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为我最好的朋友在这船上\N{\rEng}'cause my best friend's on this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.69,0:36:19.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,你们这是要杀人\N{\rEng}You'll all be responsible for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.79,0:36:20.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,把他弄出去\N{\rEng}Get him out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.85,0:36:23.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,随你怎么做  把他弄出去\N{\rEng}Do whatever you want, but get him off my case!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.89,0:36:26.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不是瞎编的  我也没疯\N{\rEng}I'm not making this up and I'm not crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.37,0:36:28.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,我说了有个人在弗吉尼亚号上\N{\rEng}If I tell you there's a man aboard the Virginian,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.65,0:36:32.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,老天爷  真的有个人在弗吉尼亚号上\N{\rEng}Jesus Christ, it means there's a man aboard the Virginian.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.29,0:36:34.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们把那破船从头到尾都清理过了\N{\rEng}We cleaned that scuttle from stem to stern.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.87,0:36:36.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,连门把手都没落下\N{\rEng}Not even doorknobs were left.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.56,0:36:38.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,只有炸药  大堆大堆的炸药\N{\rEng}Only dynamite. Dynamite! Lots of dynamite.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.86,0:36:40.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么就这么肯定船上有个人\N{\rEng}How can you be so sure that's a man on board?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.74,0:36:42.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,你要是有证据  就拿出来\N{\rEng}If you've any proof, out with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.71,0:36:45.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为负责引爆的人是我\N{\rEng}Because I'm the horse's arse who has to throw that switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.10,0:36:46.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,我确定他在里面\N{\rEng}I'm sure he's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.03,0:36:51.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,我人生最好年月就是在弗吉尼亚号上度过的\N{\rEng}I spent the best years of my life on the Virginian.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.25,0:37:28.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,收工了  伙计们\N{\rEng}End of the line boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.39,0:37:53.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,好样的\N{\rEng}Right! Bring it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.47,0:39:37.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,你演奏时到底在想什么\N{\rEng}What the hell do you think about when you're playing?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.06,0:39:41.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,手指碰触琴键的时候  你神游去了哪\N{\rEng}Where does your mind go? When you hit the keys?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.98,0:39:45.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,昨夜我去了一个美丽的国度\N{\rEng}Last night I was in a beautiful country.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.91,0:39:49.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,女人的头发上喷着香水  一切都闪闪发光\N{\rEng}Women had perfume in their hair. Everything glowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.54,0:39:52.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,到处都是老虎\N{\rEng}And it was full of tigers.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.01,0:39:54.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,他旅行\N{\rEng}He traveled.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.54,0:39:57.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,每次他都会去不同的地方\N{\rEng}And each time he ended up someplace different.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.40,0:40:01.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,伦敦市中心  哪个国家内陆的一列火车上\N{\rEng}In the heart of London, on a train in the middle of the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.52,0:40:03.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,一座巨大火山的边缘\N{\rEng}on the edge of a giant volcano,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.19,0:40:06.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,或是在世界上最大的教堂里\N{\rEng}in the biggest church in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.89,0:40:11.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,数着教堂的柱子  仰望着十字架\N{\rEng}counting the columns and staring up at the crucifixes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.19,0:40:13.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,他到处旅行\N{\rEng}He travelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.64,0:40:21.18,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}意大利南部的一种轻快民间舞曲
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.64,0:40:17.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,伙计  来首{\u1}塔兰台拉舞曲{\u0}{\fs14}[意大利语]\N{\rEng}Guaglio', facci sentire una bella tarantella!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.96,0:40:21.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,你倒说说什么叫塔兰台拉舞曲{\fs14}[意大利语]\N{\rEng}E tu fammi capire come fa questa tarantella, paisa'!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.91,0:41:30.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,美国\N{\rEng}America!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.71,0:41:58.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么不下船  就一次也好啊\N{\rEng}Why the hell don't you get off? Just once? One time?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.61,0:42:03.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,亲眼去看看这个世界\N{\rEng}See the world for yourself with your own eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.38,0:42:09.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,想过吗  你可以做任何你想做的事\N{\rEng}You ever think about it? You could do anything you wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.66,0:42:12.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,人们会为你疯狂的\N{\rEng}People would go crazy for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.97,0:42:16.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,你能赚很多钱  伙计\N{\rEng}You could make beaucoup bucks, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.87,0:42:21.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,买最好的房子  找个老婆\N{\rEng}Get yourself the finest house, get yourself a wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.70,0:42:23.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不试试呢\N{\rEng}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.89,0:42:31.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,天知道你不能一辈子\N{\rEng}God knows you can't spend the rest of your life
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.67,0:42:34.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,像溜溜球一样来回航行\N{\rEng}traveling back and forth like some yo-yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.23,0:42:35.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,世界就在陆地上\N{\rEng}The world is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.84,0:42:39.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,只有一段舷梯的距离\N{\rEng}Nothing but a gangplank to cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.06,0:42:42.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,舷梯是什么  就那么几步路而已\N{\rEng}And what's a gangplank? A few stupid steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.78,0:42:46.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,天哪  一切都在那几步路尽头等着呢\N{\rEng}Christ, everything is waiting at the bottom of those steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.15,0:42:48.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不去呢\N{\rEng}Why don't you just do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.90,0:42:50.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,就一次\N{\rEng}One time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.98,0:42:54.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不下船呢\N{\rEng}Why don't you just get off?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.58,0:43:03.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么  为什么  为什么\N{\rEng}Why? Why? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.82,0:43:04.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么  为什么\N{\rEng}Why? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.05,0:43:08.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你们陆上的人\N{\rEng}I think you land people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.53,0:43:12.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,浪费了很多时间琢磨为什么\N{\rEng}waste a lot of time wondering why.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.70,0:43:17.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,冬天到了  就急切地盼望夏天\N{\rEng}Winter comes and you can't wait for summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.54,0:43:20.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,夏天来了  又担心冬天将至\N{\rEng}Summer comes and you live in dread of winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.48,0:43:24.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以你们永远不厌烦旅行\N{\rEng}That's way you never tire of traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.20,0:43:29.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,总在追寻遥远的四季如夏的地方\N{\rEng}Always chasing someplace far away where it's always summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.38,0:43:35.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得这种地方根本找不到呢\N{\rEng}Doesn't sound like a good bet to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.87,0:43:51.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,等等  都停下\N{\rEng}Hold it, stop everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.66,0:45:08.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,原谅我的情不自禁\N{\rEng}Forgive me for allowing myself to,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.68,0:45:10.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,你的音乐太棒了\N{\rEng}your music was so strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.06,0:45:25.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,来支烟吗\N{\rEng}Want a cicca?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.12,0:45:32.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好像对去美国不怎么高兴\N{\rEng}You don't look too happy to be going to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.93,0:45:34.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是因为美国\N{\rEng}It's not America.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.23,0:45:42.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,是我舍弃的一切\N{\rEng}It's everything I leave behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.11,0:45:47.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,直到几年前  我只知道我的地\N{\rEng}Until a few years ago I know only my field.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.39,0:45:49.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,对我而言  世界始于\N{\rEng}The world for me started
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.79,0:45:52.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,并终于那块小小的土地\N{\rEng}and ended there in that little piece of the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.04,0:45:55.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,我从没踏上过城市的大街\N{\rEng}I never walked down the main street of a city.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.73,0:46:00.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,也许你无法理解  但是...\N{\rEng}Maybe you can't understand, but....
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.23,0:46:02.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,我完全理解\N{\rEng}I understand that perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.88,0:46:08.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,我认识一个有过类似境遇的人\N{\rEng}I know someone who went through something very similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.47,0:46:12.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,那他的地也突然干涸了吗\N{\rEng}And one fine day did his field go dry, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.79,0:46:15.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,他的妻子也跟神父跑了吗\N{\rEng}And did his wife also run off with a priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.48,0:46:23.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,他的五个孩子也因高烧丧命了吗\N{\rEng}And did the fever take his five children?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.32,0:46:26.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有  但他最终也是孤身一人\N{\rEng}No. But he ended up alone, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.88,0:46:31.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,那他比我幸运\N{\rEng}Then he is more lucky than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.21,0:46:35.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,我还有个女儿  小女儿\N{\rEng}I still have a daughter. The young one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.90,0:46:37.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,她幸存下来了\N{\rEng}She survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.55,0:46:38.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,也就是为了她\N{\rEng}And it's for her
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.65,0:46:43.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,我有一天决定跟我的坏运气抗争\N{\rEng}that I decide one day to fight against my bad luck,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.51,0:46:46.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,我到处走  毫无目标\N{\rEng}and travel all over without a destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.13,0:46:49.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后有一天\N{\rEng}And then one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.84,0:46:55.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,我又路过一个从未去过的小镇\N{\rEng}when I go through one of the many towns I never see before,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.06,0:46:57.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,我爬上了一座山\N{\rEng}I come to a hill,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.76,0:47:00.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后我看到了\N{\rEng}and then I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.13,0:47:03.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,我一生中见过的最美的东西\N{\rEng}the most beautiful thing in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.02,0:47:05.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,大海\N{\rEng}The sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.72,0:47:07.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,大海吗\N{\rEng}The sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.70,0:47:10.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我之前从没见过\N{\rEng}I never see it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.66,0:47:15.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,我就像被闪电击中了\N{\rEng}It was like lightning hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.48,0:47:17.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为我听到了那声音\N{\rEng}Because I hear the voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.28,0:47:20.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,大海的声音吗\N{\rEng}The voice of the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.70,0:47:22.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,对  大海的声音\N{\rEng}Yeah, the voice of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.08,0:47:26.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,我从没听到过\N{\rEng}I've never heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.00,0:47:31.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,大海的声音  就像是喊叫声\N{\rEng}The voice of the sea, it is like a shout.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.51,0:47:34.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,一声嘹亮而坚定的呼喊\N{\rEng}A shout big and strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.26,0:47:36.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,不停地大喊\N{\rEng}screaming and screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.19,0:47:38.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,它喊的是\N{\rEng}And the thing it was screaming was:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.74,0:47:39.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,你\N{\rEng}"You!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.37,0:47:45.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,一脑子屎的家伙\N{\rEng}With shit instead brains!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.82,0:47:50.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,生活是无限的  明白吗\N{\rEng}life is immense, can you understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.46,0:47:53.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,无限的\N{\rEng}Immense!"
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.72,0:47:56.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,我从没那么想过\N{\rEng}I never think of it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.17,0:47:59.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,我脑子里爆发了革命\N{\rEng}A revolution was in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.34,0:48:04.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以我突然决定改变我的生活\N{\rEng}That's how I suddenly decide to change my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.47,0:48:08.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,重新开始\N{\rEng}to start fresh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.03,0:48:12.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,改变生活  重新开始\N{\rEng}Change life. Start fresh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.72,0:48:14.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,把这话告诉你朋友\N{\rEng}Tell that to your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.49,0:48:16.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,1900\N{\rEng}1900!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.99,0:48:21.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,1900\N{\rEng}1900!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.00,0:48:26.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,是你的朋友  麦克斯·图尼\N{\rEng}It's Max Tooney, your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.64,0:48:31.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,快出来  1900  我也是你的朋友\N{\rEng}Come on out, Nineteen Hundred! I'm your friend, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.07,0:48:33.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,虽然我们从没见过\N{\rEng}Even if we've never met.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.25,0:48:36.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,别担心  这里没有警察\N{\rEng}Don't worry, no cops!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.80,0:48:49.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,你说有架钢琴是吧  具体在什么位置\N{\rEng}You said something about a piano. Where was it exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.86,0:48:51.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们在那儿发现的\N{\rEng}We found it over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.98,0:48:59.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,1900\N{\rEng}Nineteen Hundred !
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.37,0:49:05.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,小提琴演奏者  比尔·道格拉斯\N{\rEng}On the violin yours truly, Bill Douglas!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.49,0:49:09.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,大号及低音号演奏者  弗莱迪·洛亚卡诺\N{\rEng}Tuba and bass, Freddie Loyacano!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.37,0:49:13.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,小号演奏者  麦克斯·图尼\N{\rEng}Max Tooney on trumpet!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.43,0:49:18.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,最后  钢琴演奏者\N{\rEng}And finally, on piano,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.95,0:49:24.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,最棒的丹尼·布德曼·T·D·莱蒙·1900\N{\rEng}Danny Boodman T.D. Lemon Nineteen Hundred the greatest!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.68,0:49:33.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,最后一次  1900\N{\rEng}For the last time Nineteen Hundred, just...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.91,0:49:35.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,就正常弹\N{\rEng}Just the normal notes
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.71,0:49:36.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,快回去啊\N{\rEng}Come on, come on, go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.90,0:50:14.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,收工了\N{\rEng}Hey, end of the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.00,0:50:22.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,从哪来的\N{\rEng}Where do you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.82,0:50:24.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.80,0:50:25.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,音乐\N{\rEng}The music.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.04,0:50:26.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,说不清楚\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.03,0:50:29.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,比方说  看见那个女人了吗\N{\rEng}You see that woman over there? For example?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.32,0:50:36.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,她看上去像是刚在年轻情人的帮助下\N{\rEng}She looks like someone who's just killed her husband
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.69,0:50:38.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,杀了自己的丈夫\N{\rEng}with the help of her lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.68,0:50:40.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在她带着家里的珠宝逃亡\N{\rEng}And now she's running off with the family jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.70,0:50:43.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,不觉得这音乐就是她吗\N{\rEng}Don't you think this music's her?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.69,0:50:45.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,该死  还真是\N{\rEng}Damn, it's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.26,0:50:50.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,看见那个人了吗\N{\rEng}You see that guy over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.47,0:50:53.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,他无法忘却\N{\rEng}He can't forget a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.35,0:50:57.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,听他的音乐\N{\rEng}Listen to his music.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.56,0:51:02.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,他脑子里装满了记忆  而他无力改变\N{\rEng}His head bursts with memories and there's nothing he can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.72,0:51:09.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,你看那个女人\N{\rEng}And look at that one there?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.36,0:51:14.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,像是个想去做修女的妓女\N{\rEng}She looks like a prostitute who's thinking of becoming a nun.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.86,0:51:20.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,不可思议\N{\rEng}That's incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.47,0:51:29.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,再看这个人\N{\rEng}Now, look at this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.93,0:51:32.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,看见他的步态了吗\N{\rEng}See how he walks?
